PJSUA

This is the reference implementation for PJSIP and PJMEDIA. PJSUA is a console based application, designed to be simple enough to be readble, but powerful enough to demonstrate all features available in PJSIP and PJMEDIA.

This file is pjsip-apps/src/pjsua/pjsua_app.c

00384 /*
00385  * Read command arguments from config file.
00386  */
00387 static int read_config_file(pj_pool_t *pool, const char *filename, 
00388                             int *app_argc, char ***app_argv)
00389 {
00390     int i;
00391     FILE *fhnd;
00392     char line[200];
00393     int argc = 0;
00394     char **argv;
00395     enum { MAX_ARGS = 128 };
00396 
00397     /* Allocate MAX_ARGS+1 (argv needs to be terminated with NULL argument) */
00398     argv = pj_pool_calloc(pool, MAX_ARGS+1, sizeof(char*));
00399     argv[argc++] = *app_argv[0];
00400 
00401     /* Open config file. */
00402     fhnd = fopen(filename, "rt");
00403     if (!fhnd) {
00404         PJ_LOG(1,(THIS_FILE, "Unable to open config file %s", filename));
00405         fflush(stdout);
00406         return -1;
00407     }
00408 
00409     /* Scan tokens in the file. */
00410     while (argc < MAX_ARGS && !feof(fhnd)) {
00411         char  *token;
00412         char  *p;
00413         const char *whitespace = " \t\r\n";
00414         char  cDelimiter;
00415         int   len, token_len;
00416         
00417         if (fgets(line, sizeof(line), fhnd) == NULL) break;
00418         
00419         // Trim ending newlines
00420         len = strlen(line);
00421         if (line[len-1]=='\n')
00422             line[--len] = '\0';
00423         if (line[len-1]=='\r')
00424             line[--len] = '\0';
00425 
00426         if (len==0) continue;
00427 
00428         for (p = line; *p != '\0' && argc < MAX_ARGS; p++) {
00429             // first, scan whitespaces
00430             while (*p != '\0' && strchr(whitespace, *p) != NULL) p++;
00431 
00432             if (*p == '\0')                 // are we done yet?
00433                 break;
00434             
00435             if (*p == '"' || *p == '\'') {    // is token a quoted string
00436                 cDelimiter = *p++;          // save quote delimiter
00437                 token = p;
00438                 
00439                 while (*p != '\0' && *p != cDelimiter) p++;
00440                 
00441                 if (*p == '\0')         // found end of the line, but,
00442                     cDelimiter = '\0';  // didn't find a matching quote
00443 
00444             } else {                    // token's not a quoted string
00445                 token = p;
00446                 
00447                 while (*p != '\0' && strchr(whitespace, *p) == NULL) p++;
00448                 
00449                 cDelimiter = *p;
00450             }
00451             
00452             *p = '\0';
00453             token_len = p-token;
00454             
00455             if (token_len > 0) {
00456                 if (*token == '#')
00457                     break;  // ignore remainder of line
00458                 
00459                 argv[argc] = pj_pool_alloc(pool, token_len + 1);
00460                 pj_memcpy(argv[argc], token, token_len + 1);
00461                 ++argc;
00462             }
00463             
00464             *p = cDelimiter;
00465         }
00466     }
00467 
00468     /* Copy arguments from command line */
00469     for (i=1; i<*app_argc && argc < MAX_ARGS; ++i)
00470         argv[argc++] = (*app_argv)[i];
00471 
00472     if (argc == MAX_ARGS && (i!=*app_argc || !feof(fhnd))) {
00473         PJ_LOG(1,(THIS_FILE, 
00474                   "Too many arguments specified in cmd line/config file"));
00475         fflush(stdout);
00476         fclose(fhnd);
00477         return -1;
00478     }
00479 
00480     fclose(fhnd);
00481 
00482     /* Assign the new command line back to the original command line. */
00483     *app_argc = argc;
00484     *app_argv = argv;
00485     return 0;
00486 
00487 }

00489 static int my_atoi(const char *cs)
00490 {
00491     pj_str_t s;
00492 
00493     pj_cstr(&s, cs);
00494     if (cs[0] == '-') {
00495         s.ptr++, s.slen--;
00496         return 0 - (int)pj_strtoul(&s);
00497     } else if (cs[0] == '+') {
00498         s.ptr++, s.slen--;
00499         return pj_strtoul(&s);
00500     } else {
00501         return pj_strtoul(&s);
00502     }
00503 }

02052     if (config->media_cfg.tx_drop_pct) {
02053         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--tx-drop-pct %d\n",
02054                         config->media_cfg.tx_drop_pct);
02055         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02056 
02057     }
02058     if (config->media_cfg.rx_drop_pct) {
02059         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--rx-drop-pct %d\n",
02060                         config->media_cfg.rx_drop_pct);
02061         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02062 
02063     }
02064 
02065 
02066     /* Start RTP port. */
02067     pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--rtp-port %d\n",
02068                     config->rtp_cfg.port);
02069     pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02070 
02071     /* Disable codec */
02072     for (i=0; i<config->codec_dis_cnt; ++i) {
02073         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--dis-codec %s\n",
02074                     config->codec_dis[i].ptr);
02075         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02076     }
02077     /* Add codec. */
02078     for (i=0; i<config->codec_cnt; ++i) {
02079         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--add-codec %s\n",
02080                     config->codec_arg[i].ptr);
02081         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02082     }
02083 
02084     pj_strcat2(&cfg, "\n#\n# User agent:\n#\n");
02085 
02086     /* Auto-answer. */
02087     if (config->auto_answer != 0) {
02088         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--auto-answer %d\n",
02089                         config->auto_answer);
02090         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02091     }
02092 
02093     /* accept-redirect */
02094     if (config->redir_op != PJSIP_REDIRECT_ACCEPT) {
02095         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--accept-redirect %d\n",
02096                         config->redir_op);
02097         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02098     }
02099 
02100     /* Max calls. */
02101     pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--max-calls %d\n",
02102                     config->cfg.max_calls);
02103     pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02104 
02105     /* Uas-duration. */
02106     if (config->duration != NO_LIMIT) {
02107         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--duration %d\n",
02108                         config->duration);
02109         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02110     }
02111 
02112     /* norefersub ? */
02113     if (config->no_refersub) {
02114         pj_strcat2(&cfg, "--norefersub\n");
02115     }
02116 
02117     if (pjsip_use_compact_form)
02118     {
02119         pj_strcat2(&cfg, "--use-compact-form\n");
02120     }
02121 
02122     if (!config->cfg.force_lr) {
02123         pj_strcat2(&cfg, "--no-force-lr\n");
02124     }
02125 
02126     pj_strcat2(&cfg, "\n#\n# Buddies:\n#\n");
02127 
02128     /* Add buddies. */
02129     for (i=0; i<config->buddy_cnt; ++i) {
02130         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--add-buddy %.*s\n",
02131                               (int)config->buddy_cfg[i].uri.slen,
02132                               config->buddy_cfg[i].uri.ptr);
02133         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02134     }
02135 
02136     /* SIP extensions. */
02137     pj_strcat2(&cfg, "\n#\n# SIP extensions:\n#\n");
02138     /* 100rel extension */
02139     if (config->cfg.require_100rel) {
02140         pj_strcat2(&cfg, "--use-100rel\n");
02141     }
02142     /* Session Timer extension */
02143     if (config->cfg.use_timer) {
02144         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--use-timer %d\n",
02145                               config->cfg.use_timer);
02146         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02147     }
02148     if (config->cfg.timer_setting.min_se != 90) {
02149         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--timer-min-se %d\n",
02150                               config->cfg.timer_setting.min_se);
02151         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02152     }
02153     if (config->cfg.timer_setting.sess_expires != PJSIP_SESS_TIMER_DEF_SE) {
02154         pj_ansi_sprintf(line, "--timer-se %d\n",
02155                               config->cfg.timer_setting.sess_expires);
02156         pj_strcat2(&cfg, line);
02157     }
02158 
02159     *(cfg.ptr + cfg.slen) = '\0';
02160     return cfg.slen;
02161 }

02172 /*
02173  * Print log of call states. Since call states may be too long for logger,
02174  * printing it is a bit tricky, it should be printed part by part as long 
02175  * as the logger can accept.
02176  */
02177 static void log_call_dump(int call_id) 
02178 {
02179     unsigned call_dump_len;
02180     unsigned part_len;
02181     unsigned part_idx;
02182     unsigned log_decor;
02183 
02184     pjsua_call_dump(call_id, PJ_TRUE, some_buf, 
02185                     sizeof(some_buf), "  ");
02186     call_dump_len = strlen(some_buf);
02187 
02188     log_decor = pj_log_get_decor();
02189     pj_log_set_decor(log_decor & ~(PJ_LOG_HAS_NEWLINE | PJ_LOG_HAS_CR));
02190     PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "\n"));
02191     pj_log_set_decor(0);
02192 
02193     part_idx = 0;
02194     part_len = PJ_LOG_MAX_SIZE-80;
02195     while (part_idx < call_dump_len) {
02196         char p_orig, *p;
02197 
02198         p = &some_buf[part_idx];
02199         if (part_idx + part_len > call_dump_len)
02200             part_len = call_dump_len - part_idx;
02201         p_orig = p[part_len];
02202         p[part_len] = '\0';
02203         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "%s", p));
02204         p[part_len] = p_orig;
02205         part_idx += part_len;
02206     }
02207     pj_log_set_decor(log_decor);
02208 }

02308 /*
02309  * Find next call when current call is disconnected or when user
02310  * press ']'
02311  */
02312 static pj_bool_t find_next_call(void)
02313 {
02314     int i, max;
02315 
02316     max = pjsua_call_get_max_count();
02317     for (i=current_call+1; i<max; ++i) {
02318         if (pjsua_call_is_active(i)) {
02319             current_call = i;
02320             return PJ_TRUE;
02321         }
02322     }
02323 
02324     for (i=0; i<current_call; ++i) {
02325         if (pjsua_call_is_active(i)) {
02326             current_call = i;
02327             return PJ_TRUE;
02328         }
02329     }
02330 
02331     current_call = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
02332     return PJ_FALSE;
02333 }

02336 /*
02337  * Find previous call when user press '['
02338  */
02339 static pj_bool_t find_prev_call(void)
02340 {
02341     int i, max;
02342 
02343     max = pjsua_call_get_max_count();
02344     for (i=current_call-1; i>=0; --i) {
02345         if (pjsua_call_is_active(i)) {
02346             current_call = i;
02347             return PJ_TRUE;
02348         }
02349     }
02350 
02351     for (i=max-1; i>current_call; --i) {
02352         if (pjsua_call_is_active(i)) {
02353             current_call = i;
02354             return PJ_TRUE;
02355         }
02356     }
02357 
02358     current_call = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
02359     return PJ_FALSE;
02360 }

02363 /* Callback from timer when the maximum call duration has been
02364  * exceeded.
02365  */
02366 static void call_timeout_callback(pj_timer_heap_t *timer_heap,
02367                                   struct pj_timer_entry *entry)
02368 {
02369     pjsua_call_id call_id = entry->id;
02370     pjsua_msg_data msg_data;
02371     pjsip_generic_string_hdr warn;
02372     pj_str_t hname = pj_str("Warning");
02373     pj_str_t hvalue = pj_str("399 pjsua \"Call duration exceeded\"");
02374 
02375     PJ_UNUSED_ARG(timer_heap);
02376 
02377     if (call_id == PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
02378         PJ_LOG(1,(THIS_FILE, "Invalid call ID in timer callback"));
02379         return;
02380     }
02381     
02382     /* Add warning header */
02383     pjsua_msg_data_init(&msg_data);
02384     pjsip_generic_string_hdr_init2(&warn, &hname, &hvalue);
02385     pj_list_push_back(&msg_data.hdr_list, &warn);
02386 
02387     /* Call duration has been exceeded; disconnect the call */
02388     PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Duration (%d seconds) has been exceeded "
02389                          "for call %d, disconnecting the call",
02390                          app_config.duration, call_id));
02391     entry->id = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
02392     pjsua_call_hangup(call_id, 200, NULL, &msg_data);
02393 }

02396 /*
02397  * Handler when invite state has changed.
02398  */
02399 static void on_call_state(pjsua_call_id call_id, pjsip_event *e)
02400 {
02401     pjsua_call_info call_info;
02402 
02403     PJ_UNUSED_ARG(e);
02404 
02405     pjsua_call_get_info(call_id, &call_info);
02406 
02407     if (call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_DISCONNECTED) {
02408 
02409         /* Stop all ringback for this call */
02410         ring_stop(call_id);
02411 
02412         /* Cancel duration timer, if any */
02413         if (app_config.call_data[call_id].timer.id != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
02414             struct call_data *cd = &app_config.call_data[call_id];
02415             pjsip_endpoint *endpt = pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt();
02416 
02417             cd->timer.id = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
02418             pjsip_endpt_cancel_timer(endpt, &cd->timer);
02419         }
02420 
02421         /* Rewind play file when hangup automatically, 
02422          * since file is not looped
02423          */
02424         if (app_config.auto_play_hangup)
02425             pjsua_player_set_pos(app_config.wav_id, 0);
02426 
02427 
02428         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d is DISCONNECTED [reason=%d (%s)]", 
02429                   call_id,
02430                   call_info.last_status,
02431                   call_info.last_status_text.ptr));
02432 
02433         if (call_id == current_call) {
02434             find_next_call();
02435         }
02436 
02437         /* Dump media state upon disconnected */
02438         if (1) {
02439             PJ_LOG(5,(THIS_FILE, 
02440                       "Call %d disconnected, dumping media stats..", 
02441                       call_id));
02442             log_call_dump(call_id);
02443         }
02444 
02445     } else {
02446 
02447         if (app_config.duration!=NO_LIMIT && 
02448             call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_CONFIRMED) 
02449         {
02450             /* Schedule timer to hangup call after the specified duration */
02451             struct call_data *cd = &app_config.call_data[call_id];
02452             pjsip_endpoint *endpt = pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt();
02453             pj_time_val delay;
02454 
02455             cd->timer.id = call_id;
02456             delay.sec = app_config.duration;
02457             delay.msec = 0;
02458             pjsip_endpt_schedule_timer(endpt, &cd->timer, &delay);
02459         }
02460 
02461         if (call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_EARLY) {
02462             int code;
02463             pj_str_t reason;
02464             pjsip_msg *msg;
02465 
02466             /* This can only occur because of TX or RX message */
02467             pj_assert(e->type == PJSIP_EVENT_TSX_STATE);
02468 
02469             if (e->body.tsx_state.type == PJSIP_EVENT_RX_MSG) {
02470                 msg = e->body.tsx_state.src.rdata->msg_info.msg;
02471             } else {
02472                 msg = e->body.tsx_state.src.tdata->msg;
02473             }
02474 
02475             code = msg->line.status.code;
02476             reason = msg->line.status.reason;
02477 
02478             /* Start ringback for 180 for UAC unless there's SDP in 180 */
02479             if (call_info.role==PJSIP_ROLE_UAC && code==180 && 
02480                 msg->body == NULL && 
02481                 call_info.media_status==PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_NONE) 
02482             {
02483                 ringback_start(call_id);
02484             }
02485 
02486             PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d state changed to %s (%d %.*s)", 
02487                       call_id, call_info.state_text.ptr,
02488                       code, (int)reason.slen, reason.ptr));
02489         } else {
02490             PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d state changed to %s", 
02491                       call_id,
02492                       call_info.state_text.ptr));
02493         }
02494 
02495         if (current_call==PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
02496             current_call = call_id;
02497 
02498     }
02499 }

02543 /*
02544  * Handler when a transaction within a call has changed state.
02545  */
02546 static void on_call_tsx_state(pjsua_call_id call_id,
02547                               pjsip_transaction *tsx,
02548                               pjsip_event *e)
02549 {
02550     const pjsip_method info_method = 
02551     {
02552         PJSIP_OTHER_METHOD,
02553         { "INFO", 4 }
02554     };
02555 
02556     if (pjsip_method_cmp(&tsx->method, &info_method)==0) {
02557         /*
02558          * Handle INFO method.
02559          */
02560         if (tsx->role == PJSIP_ROLE_UAC && 
02561             (tsx->state == PJSIP_TSX_STATE_COMPLETED ||
02562                (tsx->state == PJSIP_TSX_STATE_TERMINATED &&
02563                 e->body.tsx_state.prev_state != PJSIP_TSX_STATE_COMPLETED))) 
02564         {
02565             /* Status of outgoing INFO request */
02566             if (tsx->status_code >= 200 && tsx->status_code < 300) {
02567                 PJ_LOG(4,(THIS_FILE, 
02568                           "Call %d: DTMF sent successfully with INFO",
02569                           call_id));
02570             } else if (tsx->status_code >= 300) {
02571                 PJ_LOG(4,(THIS_FILE, 
02572                           "Call %d: Failed to send DTMF with INFO: %d/%.*s",
02573                           call_id,
02574                           tsx->status_code,
02575                           (int)tsx->status_text.slen,
02576                           tsx->status_text.ptr));
02577             }
02578         } else if (tsx->role == PJSIP_ROLE_UAS &&
02579                    tsx->state == PJSIP_TSX_STATE_TRYING)
02580         {
02581             /* Answer incoming INFO with 200/OK */
02582             pjsip_rx_data *rdata;
02583             pjsip_tx_data *tdata;
02584             pj_status_t status;
02585 
02586             rdata = e->body.tsx_state.src.rdata;
02587 
02588             if (rdata->msg_info.msg->body) {
02589                 status = pjsip_endpt_create_response(tsx->endpt, rdata,
02590                                                      200, NULL, &tdata);
02591                 if (status == PJ_SUCCESS)
02592                     status = pjsip_tsx_send_msg(tsx, tdata);
02593 
02594                 PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d: incoming INFO:\n%.*s", 
02595                           call_id,
02596                           (int)rdata->msg_info.msg->body->len,
02597                           rdata->msg_info.msg->body->data));
02598             } else {
02599                 status = pjsip_endpt_create_response(tsx->endpt, rdata,
02600                                                      400, NULL, &tdata);
02601                 if (status == PJ_SUCCESS)
02602                     status = pjsip_tsx_send_msg(tsx, tdata);
02603             }
02604         }
02605     }
02606 }

02609 /*
02610  * Callback on media state changed event.
02611  * The action may connect the call to sound device, to file, or
02612  * to loop the call.
02613  */
02614 static void on_call_media_state(pjsua_call_id call_id)
02615 {
02616     pjsua_call_info call_info;
02617 
02618     pjsua_call_get_info(call_id, &call_info);
02619 
02620     /* Stop ringback */
02621     ring_stop(call_id);
02622 
02623     /* Connect ports appropriately when media status is ACTIVE or REMOTE HOLD,
02624      * otherwise we should NOT connect the ports.
02625      */
02626     if (call_info.media_status == PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_ACTIVE ||
02627         call_info.media_status == PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_REMOTE_HOLD)
02628     {
02629         pj_bool_t connect_sound = PJ_TRUE;
02630 
02631         /* Loopback sound, if desired */
02632         if (app_config.auto_loop) {
02633             pjsua_conf_connect(call_info.conf_slot, call_info.conf_slot);
02634             connect_sound = PJ_FALSE;
02635         }
02636 
02637         /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
02638         if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
02639             pjsua_conf_connect(call_info.conf_slot, app_config.rec_port);
02640         }
02641 
02642         /* Stream a file, if desired */
02643         if ((app_config.auto_play || app_config.auto_play_hangup) && 
02644             app_config.wav_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
02645         {
02646             pjsua_conf_connect(app_config.wav_port, call_info.conf_slot);
02647             connect_sound = PJ_FALSE;
02648         }
02649 
02650         /* Put call in conference with other calls, if desired */
02651         if (app_config.auto_conf) {
02652             pjsua_call_id call_ids[PJSUA_MAX_CALLS];
02653             unsigned call_cnt=PJ_ARRAY_SIZE(call_ids);
02654             unsigned i;
02655 
02656             /* Get all calls, and establish media connection between
02657              * this call and other calls.
02658              */
02659             pjsua_enum_calls(call_ids, &call_cnt);
02660 
02661             for (i=0; i<call_cnt; ++i) {
02662                 if (call_ids[i] == call_id)
02663                     continue;
02664                 
02665                 if (!pjsua_call_has_media(call_ids[i]))
02666                     continue;
02667 
02668                 pjsua_conf_connect(call_info.conf_slot,
02669                                    pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]));
02670                 pjsua_conf_connect(pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]),
02671                                    call_info.conf_slot);
02672 
02673                 /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
02674                 if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
02675                     pjsua_conf_connect(pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]), 
02676                                        app_config.rec_port);
02677                 }
02678 
02679             }
02680 
02681             /* Also connect call to local sound device */
02682             connect_sound = PJ_TRUE;
02683         }
02684 
02685         /* Otherwise connect to sound device */
02686         if (connect_sound) {
02687             pjsua_conf_connect(call_info.conf_slot, 0);
02688             pjsua_conf_connect(0, call_info.conf_slot);
02689 
02690             /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
02691             if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
02692                 pjsua_conf_connect(call_info.conf_slot, app_config.rec_port);
02693                 pjsua_conf_connect(0, app_config.rec_port);
02694             }
02695         }
02696     }
02697 
02698     /* Handle media status */
02699     switch (call_info.media_status) {
02700     case PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_ACTIVE:
02701         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Media for call %d is active", call_id));
02702         break;
02703 
02704     case PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_LOCAL_HOLD:
02705         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Media for call %d is suspended (hold) by local",
02706                   call_id));
02707         break;
02708 
02709     case PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_REMOTE_HOLD:
02710         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, 
02711                   "Media for call %d is suspended (hold) by remote",
02712                   call_id));
02713         break;
02714 
02715     case PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_ERROR:
02716         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE,
02717                   "Media has reported error, disconnecting call"));
02718         {
02719             pj_str_t reason = pj_str("ICE negotiation failed");
02720             pjsua_call_hangup(call_id, 500, &reason, NULL);
02721         }
02722         break;
02723 
02724     case PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_NONE:
02725         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, 
02726                   "Media for call %d is inactive",
02727                   call_id));
02728         break;
02729 
02730     default:
02731         pj_assert(!"Unhandled media status");
02732         break;
02733     }
02734 }

02984 /*
02985  * Transport status notification
02986  */
02987 static void on_transport_state(pjsip_transport *tp, 
02988                                pjsip_transport_state state,
02989                                const pjsip_transport_state_info *info)
02990 {
02991     char host_port[128];
02992 
02993     pj_ansi_snprintf(host_port, sizeof(host_port), "[%.*s:%d]",
02994                      (int)tp->remote_name.host.slen,
02995                      tp->remote_name.host.ptr,
02996                      tp->remote_name.port);
02997 
02998     switch (state) {
02999     case PJSIP_TP_STATE_CONNECTED:
03000         {
03001             PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "SIP %s transport is connected to %s",
03002                      tp->type_name, host_port));
03003         }
03004         break;
03005 
03006     case PJSIP_TP_STATE_DISCONNECTED:
03007         {
03008             char buf[100];
03009 
03010             snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "SIP %s transport is disconnected from %s",
03011                      tp->type_name, host_port);
03012             pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, buf, info->status);
03013         }
03014         break;
03015 
03016     default:
03017         break;
03018     }
03019 
03020 #if defined(PJSIP_HAS_TLS_TRANSPORT) && PJSIP_HAS_TLS_TRANSPORT!=0
03021 
03022     if (!pj_ansi_stricmp(tp->type_name, "tls") && info->ext_info &&
03023         (state == PJSIP_TP_STATE_CONNECTED || 
03024          ((pjsip_tls_state_info*)info->ext_info)->
03025                                  ssl_sock_info->verify_status != PJ_SUCCESS))
03026     {
03027         pjsip_tls_state_info *tls_info = (pjsip_tls_state_info*)info->ext_info;
03028         pj_ssl_sock_info *ssl_sock_info = tls_info->ssl_sock_info;
03029         char buf[2048];
03030         const char *verif_msgs[32];
03031         unsigned verif_msg_cnt;
03032 
03033         /* Dump server TLS cipher */
03034         PJ_LOG(4,(THIS_FILE, "TLS cipher used: 0x%06X/%s",
03035                   ssl_sock_info->cipher,
03036                   pj_ssl_cipher_name(ssl_sock_info->cipher) ));
03037 
03038         /* Dump server TLS certificate */
03039         pj_ssl_cert_info_dump(ssl_sock_info->remote_cert_info, "  ",
03040                               buf, sizeof(buf));
03041         PJ_LOG(4,(THIS_FILE, "TLS cert info of %s:\n%s", host_port, buf));
03042 
03043         /* Dump server TLS certificate verification result */
03044         verif_msg_cnt = PJ_ARRAY_SIZE(verif_msgs);
03045         pj_ssl_cert_get_verify_status_strings(ssl_sock_info->verify_status,
03046                                               verif_msgs, &verif_msg_cnt);
03047         PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "TLS cert verification result of %s : %s",
03048                              host_port,
03049                              (verif_msg_cnt == 1? verif_msgs[0]:"")));
03050         if (verif_msg_cnt > 1) {
03051             unsigned i;
03052             for (i = 0; i < verif_msg_cnt; ++i)
03053                 PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "- %s", verif_msgs[i]));
03054         }
03055 
03056         if (ssl_sock_info->verify_status &&
03057             !app_config.udp_cfg.tls_setting.verify_server) 
03058         {
03059             PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "PJSUA is configured to ignore TLS cert "
03060                                  "verification errors"));
03061         }
03062     }
03063 
03064 #endif
03065 
03066 }

03269 /*
03270  * Input simple string
03271  */
03272 static pj_bool_t simple_input(const char *title, char *buf, pj_size_t len)
03273 {
03274     char *p;
03275 
03276     printf("%s (empty to cancel): ", title); fflush(stdout);
03277     if (fgets(buf, len, stdin) == NULL)
03278         return PJ_FALSE;
03279 
03280     /* Remove trailing newlines. */
03281     for (p=buf; ; ++p) {
03282         if (*p=='\r' || *p=='\n') *p='\0';
03283         else if (!*p) break;
03284     }
03285 
03286     if (!*buf)
03287         return PJ_FALSE;
03288     
03289     return PJ_TRUE;
03290 }

03301 /*
03302  * Input URL.
03303  */
03304 static void ui_input_url(const char *title, char *buf, int len, 
03305                          struct input_result *result)
03306 {
03307     result->nb_result = NO_NB;
03308     result->uri_result = NULL;
03309 
03310     print_buddy_list();
03311 
03312     printf("Choices:\n"
03313            "   0         For current dialog.\n"
03314            "  -1         All %d buddies in buddy list\n"
03315            "  [1 -%2d]    Select from buddy list\n"
03316            "  URL        An URL\n"
03317            "  <Enter>    Empty input (or 'q') to cancel\n"
03318            , pjsua_get_buddy_count(), pjsua_get_buddy_count());
03319     printf("%s: ", title);
03320 
03321     fflush(stdout);
03322     if (fgets(buf, len, stdin) == NULL)
03323         return;
03324     len = strlen(buf);
03325 
03326     /* Left trim */
03327     while (pj_isspace(*buf)) {
03328         ++buf;
03329         --len;
03330     }
03331 
03332     /* Remove trailing newlines */
03333     while (len && (buf[len-1] == '\r' || buf[len-1] == '\n'))
03334         buf[--len] = '\0';
03335 
03336     if (len == 0 || buf[0]=='q')
03337         return;
03338 
03339     if (pj_isdigit(*buf) || *buf=='-') {
03340         
03341         int i;
03342         
03343         if (*buf=='-')
03344             i = 1;
03345         else
03346             i = 0;
03347 
03348         for (; i<len; ++i) {
03349             if (!pj_isdigit(buf[i])) {
03350                 puts("Invalid input");
03351                 return;
03352             }
03353         }
03354 
03355         result->nb_result = my_atoi(buf);
03356 
03357         if (result->nb_result >= 0 && 
03358             result->nb_result <= (int)pjsua_get_buddy_count()) 
03359         {
03360             return;
03361         }
03362         if (result->nb_result == -1)
03363             return;
03364 
03365         puts("Invalid input");
03366         result->nb_result = NO_NB;
03367         return;
03368 
03369     } else {
03370         pj_status_t status;
03371 
03372         if ((status=pjsua_verify_url(buf)) != PJ_SUCCESS) {
03373             pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, "Invalid URL", status);
03374             return;
03375         }
03376 
03377         result->uri_result = buf;
03378     }
03379 }

03526 /*
03527  * Change codec priorities.
03528  */
03529 static void manage_codec_prio(void)
03530 {
03531     pjsua_codec_info c[32];
03532     unsigned i, count = PJ_ARRAY_SIZE(c);
03533     char input[32];
03534     char *codec, *prio;
03535     pj_str_t id;
03536     int new_prio;
03537     pj_status_t status;
03538 
03539     printf("List of codecs:\n");
03540 
03541     pjsua_enum_codecs(c, &count);
03542     for (i=0; i<count; ++i) {
03543         printf("  %d\t%.*s\n", c[i].priority, (int)c[i].codec_id.slen,
03544                                c[i].codec_id.ptr);
03545     }
03546 
03547     puts("");
03548     puts("Enter codec id and its new priority "
03549          "(e.g. \"speex/16000 200\"), empty to cancel:");
03550 
03551     printf("Codec name (\"*\" for all) and priority: ");
03552     if (fgets(input, sizeof(input), stdin) == NULL)
03553         return;
03554     if (input[0]=='\r' || input[0]=='\n') {
03555         puts("Done");
03556         return;
03557     }
03558 
03559     codec = strtok(input, " \t\r\n");
03560     prio = strtok(NULL, " \r\n");
03561 
03562     if (!codec || !prio) {
03563         puts("Invalid input");
03564         return;
03565     }
03566 
03567     new_prio = atoi(prio);
03568     if (new_prio < 0) 
03569         new_prio = 0;
03570     else if (new_prio > PJMEDIA_CODEC_PRIO_HIGHEST) 
03571         new_prio = PJMEDIA_CODEC_PRIO_HIGHEST;
03572 
03573     status = pjsua_codec_set_priority(pj_cstr(&id, codec), 
03574                                       (pj_uint8_t)new_prio);
03575     if (status != PJ_SUCCESS)
03576         pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, "Error setting codec priority", status);
03577 }

04569 /*****************************************************************************
04570  * A simple module to handle otherwise unhandled request. We will register
04571  * this with the lowest priority.
04572  */
04573 
04574 /* Notification on incoming request */
04575 static pj_bool_t default_mod_on_rx_request(pjsip_rx_data *rdata)
04576 {
04577     pjsip_tx_data *tdata;
04578     pjsip_status_code status_code;
04579     pj_status_t status;
04580 
04581     /* Don't respond to ACK! */
04582     if (pjsip_method_cmp(&rdata->msg_info.msg->line.req.method, 
04583                          &pjsip_ack_method) == 0)
04584         return PJ_TRUE;
04585 
04586     /* Create basic response. */
04587     if (pjsip_method_cmp(&rdata->msg_info.msg->line.req.method, 
04588                          &pjsip_notify_method) == 0)
04589     {
04590         /* Unsolicited NOTIFY's, send with Bad Request */
04591         status_code = PJSIP_SC_BAD_REQUEST;
04592     } else {
04593         /* Probably unknown method */
04594         status_code = PJSIP_SC_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED;
04595     }
04596     status = pjsip_endpt_create_response(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(), 
04597                                          rdata, status_code, 
04598                                          NULL, &tdata);
04599     if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
04600         pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, "Unable to create response", status);
04601         return PJ_TRUE;
04602     }
04603 
04604     /* Add Allow if we're responding with 405 */
04605     if (status_code == PJSIP_SC_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED) {
04606         const pjsip_hdr *cap_hdr;
04607         cap_hdr = pjsip_endpt_get_capability(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(), 
04608                                              PJSIP_H_ALLOW, NULL);
04609         if (cap_hdr) {
04610             pjsip_msg_add_hdr(tdata->msg, pjsip_hdr_clone(tdata->pool, 
04611                                                            cap_hdr));
04612         }
04613     }
04614 
04615     /* Add User-Agent header */
04616     {
04617         pj_str_t user_agent;
04618         char tmp[80];
04619         const pj_str_t USER_AGENT = { "User-Agent", 10};
04620         pjsip_hdr *h;
04621 
04622         pj_ansi_snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "PJSUA v%s/%s", 
04623                          pj_get_version(), PJ_OS_NAME);
04624         pj_strdup2_with_null(tdata->pool, &user_agent, tmp);
04625 
04626         h = (pjsip_hdr*) pjsip_generic_string_hdr_create(tdata->pool,
04627                                                          &USER_AGENT,
04628                                                          &user_agent);
04629         pjsip_msg_add_hdr(tdata->msg, h);
04630     }
04631 
04632     pjsip_endpt_send_response2(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(), rdata, tdata, 
04633                                NULL, NULL);
04634 
04635     return PJ_TRUE;
04636 }

05052 static int stdout_refresh_proc(void *arg)
05053 {
05054     PJ_UNUSED_ARG(arg);
05055 
05056     /* Set thread to lowest priority so that it doesn't clobber
05057      * stdout output
05058      */
05059     pj_thread_set_prio(pj_thread_this(), 
05060                        pj_thread_get_prio_min(pj_thread_this()));
05061 
05062     while (!stdout_refresh_quit) {
05063         pj_thread_sleep(stdout_refresh * 1000);
05064         puts(stdout_refresh_text);
05065         fflush(stdout);
05066     }
05067 
05068     return 0;
05069 }

05071 pj_status_t app_main(void)
05072 {
05073     pj_thread_t *stdout_refresh_thread = NULL;
05074     pj_status_t status;
05075 
05076     /* Start pjsua */
05077     status = pjsua_start();
05078     if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
05079         app_destroy();
05080         return status;
05081     }
05082 
05083     /* Start console refresh thread */
05084     if (stdout_refresh > 0) {
05085         pj_thread_create(app_config.pool, "stdout", &stdout_refresh_proc,
05086                          NULL, 0, 0, &stdout_refresh_thread);
05087     }
05088 
05089     console_app_main(&uri_arg);
05090 
05091     if (stdout_refresh_thread) {
05092         stdout_refresh_quit = PJ_TRUE;
05093         pj_thread_join(stdout_refresh_thread);
05094         pj_thread_destroy(stdout_refresh_thread);
05095     }
05096 
05097     return PJ_SUCCESS;
05098 }

05104 
05105 #ifdef STEREO_DEMO

05117         pjmedia_port_destroy(app_config.sc);
05118         app_config.sc = NULL;
05119     }
05120 #endif
05121 
05122     /* Close ringback port */
05123     if (app_config.ringback_port && 
05124         app_config.ringback_slot != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) 
05125     {
05126         pjsua_conf_remove_port(app_config.ringback_slot);
05127         app_config.ringback_slot = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
05128         pjmedia_port_destroy(app_config.ringback_port);
05129         app_config.ringback_port = NULL;
05130     }
05131 
05132     /* Close ring port */
05133     if (app_config.ring_port && app_config.ring_slot != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
05134         pjsua_conf_remove_port(app_config.ring_slot);
05135         app_config.ring_slot = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
05136         pjmedia_port_destroy(app_config.ring_port);
05137         app_config.ring_port = NULL;

05141     for (i=0; i<app_config.tone_count; ++i) {

05144 
05145     if (app_config.pool) {
05146         pj_pool_release(app_config.pool);
05147         app_config.pool = NULL;
05148     }
05149 
05150     status = pjsua_destroy();
05151 
05152     pj_bzero(&app_config, sizeof(app_config));
05153 
05154     return status;
05155 }

05158 #ifdef STEREO_DEMO
05159 /*
05160  * In this stereo demo, we open the sound device in stereo mode and
05161  * arrange the attachment to the PJSUA-LIB conference bridge as such
05162  * so that channel0/left channel of the sound device corresponds to
05163  * slot 0 in the bridge, and channel1/right channel of the sound
05164  * device corresponds to slot 1 in the bridge. Then user can independently
05165  * feed different media to/from the speakers/microphones channels, by
05166  * connecting them to slot 0 or 1 respectively.
05167  *
05168  * Here's how the connection looks like:
05169  *
05170    +-----------+ stereo +-----------------+ 2x mono +-----------+
05171    | AUDIO DEV |<------>| SPLITCOMB   left|<------->|#0  BRIDGE |
05172    +-----------+        |            right|<------->|#1         |
05173                         +-----------------+         +-----------+
05174  */
05175 static void stereo_demo()
05176 {
05177     pjmedia_port *conf;
05178     pj_status_t status;
05179 
05180     /* Disable existing sound device */
05181     conf = pjsua_set_no_snd_dev();
05182 
05183     /* Create stereo-mono splitter/combiner */
05184     status = pjmedia_splitcomb_create(app_config.pool, 
05185                                       conf->info.clock_rate /* clock rate */,
05186                                       2     /* stereo */,
05187                                       2 * conf->info.samples_per_frame,
05188                                       conf->info.bits_per_sample,
05189                                       0     /* options */,
05190                                       &app_config.sc);
05191     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05192 
05193     /* Connect channel0 (left channel?) to conference port slot0 */
05194     status = pjmedia_splitcomb_set_channel(app_config.sc, 0 /* ch0 */, 
05195                                            0 /*options*/,
05196                                            conf);
05197     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05198 
05199     /* Create reverse channel for channel1 (right channel?)... */
05200     status = pjmedia_splitcomb_create_rev_channel(app_config.pool,
05201                                                   app_config.sc,
05202                                                   1  /* ch1 */,
05203                                                   0  /* options */,
05204                                                   &app_config.sc_ch1);
05205     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05206 
05207     /* .. and register it to conference bridge (it would be slot1
05208      * if there's no other devices connected to the bridge)
05209      */
05210     status = pjsua_conf_add_port(app_config.pool, app_config.sc_ch1, 
05211                                  &app_config.sc_ch1_slot);
05212     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05213     
05214     /* Create sound device */
05215     status = pjmedia_snd_port_create(app_config.pool, -1, -1, 
05216                                      conf->info.clock_rate,
05217                                      2      /* stereo */,
05218                                      2 * conf->info.samples_per_frame,
05219                                      conf->info.bits_per_sample,
05220                                      0, &app_config.snd);
05221     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05222 
05223 
05224     /* Connect the splitter to the sound device */
05225     status = pjmedia_snd_port_connect(app_config.snd, app_config.sc);
05226     pj_assert(status == PJ_SUCCESS);
05227 
05228 }

05230 
05231 static pj_status_t create_ipv6_media_transports(void)
05232 {
05233     pjsua_media_transport tp[PJSUA_MAX_CALLS];
05234     pj_status_t status;
05235     int port = app_config.rtp_cfg.port;
05236     unsigned i;
05237 
05238     for (i=0; i<app_config.cfg.max_calls; ++i) {
05239         enum { MAX_RETRY = 10 };
05240         pj_sock_t sock[2];
05241         pjmedia_sock_info si;
05242         unsigned j;
05243 
05244         /* Get rid of uninitialized var compiler warning with MSVC */
05245         status = PJ_SUCCESS;
05246 
05247         for (j=0; j<MAX_RETRY; ++j) {
05248             unsigned k;
05249 
05250             for (k=0; k<2; ++k) {
05251                 pj_sockaddr bound_addr;
05252 
05253                 status = pj_sock_socket(pj_AF_INET6(), pj_SOCK_DGRAM(), 0, &sock[k]);
05254                 if (status != PJ_SUCCESS)
05255                     break;
05256 
05257                 status = pj_sockaddr_init(pj_AF_INET6(), &bound_addr,
05258                                           &app_config.rtp_cfg.bound_addr, 
05259                                           (unsigned short)(port+k));
05260                 if (status != PJ_SUCCESS)
05261                     break;
05262 
05263                 status = pj_sock_bind(sock[k], &bound_addr, 
05264                                       pj_sockaddr_get_len(&bound_addr));
05265                 if (status != PJ_SUCCESS)
05266                     break;
05267             }
05268             if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
05269                 if (k==1)
05270                     pj_sock_close(sock[0]);
05271 
05272                 if (port != 0)
05273                     port += 10;
05274                 else
05275                     break;
05276 
05277                 continue;
05278             }
05279 
05280             pj_bzero(&si, sizeof(si));
05281             si.rtp_sock = sock[0];
05282             si.rtcp_sock = sock[1];
05283         
05284             pj_sockaddr_init(pj_AF_INET6(), &si.rtp_addr_name, 
05285                              &app_config.rtp_cfg.public_addr, 
05286                              (unsigned short)(port));
05287             pj_sockaddr_init(pj_AF_INET6(), &si.rtcp_addr_name, 
05288                              &app_config.rtp_cfg.public_addr, 
05289                              (unsigned short)(port+1));
05290 
05291             status = pjmedia_transport_udp_attach(pjsua_get_pjmedia_endpt(),
05292                                                   NULL,
05293                                                   &si,
05294                                                   0,
05295                                                   &tp[i].transport);
05296             if (port != 0)
05297                 port += 10;
05298             else
05299                 break;
05300 
05301             if (status == PJ_SUCCESS)
05302                 break;
05303         }
05304 
05305         if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
05306             pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, "Error creating IPv6 UDP media transport", 
05307                          status);
05308             for (j=0; j<i; ++j) {
05309                 pjmedia_transport_close(tp[j].transport);
05310             }
05311             return status;
05312         }
05313     }
05314 
05315     return pjsua_media_transports_attach(tp, i, PJ_TRUE);
05316 }
